<?xml-model ../out/tls1.rnc application/relax-ng-compact-syntax?><div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:mods="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3" xmlns:tls="http://tls.kanripo.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" type="concept" xml:id="uuid-ed834c91-0d7b-4239-8a1f-d699db6202dc"><head>WEEK</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">星期</item><item xml:lang="och">旬</item></list><div type="definition"><p>PERIOD of TYPICALLY 7 OR 10 DAYS into which the MONTH is DIVIDED.</p></div><div type="notes"><div type="old-chinese-criteria"><p>1. The general term for the ten-day week, or decameron, was xún 旬 which is already current on OBI, being an important dimension of the organisation of Shāng dynasty state rituals.</p></div><div type="modern-chinese-criteria"><p>星期</p><p>周</p><p>禮拜</p><p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div><div type="pointers"><list type="mereonymy"><item><ref target="#uuid-96e70cb3-5bb8-4cce-94ce-251c2bdc9b30">DAY</ref></item></list></div><div type="source-references"><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-60d39cc0-d76b-4275-8490-886ace4204be">BUCK 1988</ref><title>A Dictionary of Selected Synonyms in the Principal Indo-European Languages</title><biblScope unit="page">14.61</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl></listBibl></div><div type="words"><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-e72a6fbb-7820-4419-8852-11979289b5f6"><form corresp="#uuid-7f15608c-0133-4b74-bed5-16b5b2b04072"><orth>旬</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">xún</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">sɢʷlin</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">zʷin</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-1bc4f9f9-d3f6-4f1f-8b05-429223e05571"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-0d5be854-fb7c-4bcb-bc61-bbcf1be20239">vi0adS</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>OBI: after having passed one decameron</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-77314bb2-8489-4ef9-be3f-da5db56c18d9"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">5</usg></gramGrp><def>OBI: ten-day-week; decameron; on of the six gānzhī 干枝 cycles of ten days each</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-107df6a2-121b-4300-9a09-6cb31b6e326d"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-15a63dd4-7a7c-4eb9-ac1c-838163d3e4bf">nadV.postN{SUBJ}</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">4</usg></gramGrp><def>in the course of the next ten-day week</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-0f8f896e-4330-44f1-86e6-67a96240c2a2"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-91666c59-4a69-460f-8cd3-9ddbff370ae5">nadV</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>in the course of a ten-day week</def></sense></entry></div></div>